headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen scored 20 points, Evan Mobley added 19 and the Cleveland Cavaliers won their fourth straight game, 113-85 over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night despite resting their starting backcourt.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen, Mobley power Cavaliers to 113-85 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored 36 points and matched a career high with eight 3-pointers, and the Washington Wizards beat the Charlotte Hornets 118-104 on Wednesday night to stop a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis makes eight 3s as Wizards beat Hornets, end skid

headlines.description: — The NBA-leading Boston Celtics scrounged enough out of their bench to keep the Philadelphia 76ers at bay in the Eastern Conference playoff race.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics lose Jaylen Brown, hold on to beat Sixers 106-99

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo entered this season wanting more shots. The Miami Heat gave him those opportunities, and are thrilled at how it's working out.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo scores 38, Heat hold off sliding Pacers 116-111

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 37 points and 10 rebounds, Fred VanVleet scored 16 points and the Toronto Raptors beat San Antonio 112-98 on Wednesday night, handing the struggling Spurs their 10th consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 37, Raptors hand Spurs 10th straight loss

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 31 points, including three free throws with less than a second left, to lift the Sacramento Kings to a 130-128 win over the Houston Rockets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox's late FTs gives Kings 130-128 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving came out charging in his Dallas debut, keying a big run to open the game and sparking his...
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving scores 24 in Dallas debut, leads Mavs over Clippers

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 33 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds as the Portland Trail Blazers rallied past the Golden State Warriors 125-122 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has triple-double, Blazers beat Warriors 125-122
